          <h2 style="font-size:20px;line-height:1.2;font-weight:500; margin-top:16px !important">Hezbollah-Israel ceasefire</h2>
        </mj-text>
         <mj-image padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.geopolitics.world/email/images/gp-nov-28-1.jpg" alt="Hezbollah-Israel ceasefire" href="https://www.geopolitics.world" />
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;">The <a href="https://www.bbc.com/news/articles/cx2d3gj9ewxo" target="_blank">ceasefire between Israel and Hezbollah</a> came into effect early Wednesday and has sparked a range of <a href="https://www.bbc.com/news/videos/c2k0ezg2p3go" target="_blank">reactions</a>. Some residents are cautiously optimistic but still note the devastation caused by the conflict, such as lost lives and destroyed homes. In Beirut, opinions on the ceasefire varied, with some expressing skepticism and calling for accountability and rebuilding. In Israel, reactions were mixed as well: some were hopeful for peace and the return of displaced residents; critics are fearing Hezbollah might regroup.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;">The ceasefire did not affect <a href="https://www.bbc.com/news/articles/c0j8063plvdo" target="_blank">Gaza</a>, but US President Joe Biden expressed his wish that one would happen sooner rather than later. <a href="https://www.timesofisrael.com/liveblog_entry/hamas-says-group-ready-for-gaza-ceasefire-after-hezbollah-appears-to-lay-down-arms/" target="_blank">Hamas</a> has also hinted it is ready for a ceasefire. The U.S. hopes the Lebanon truce, which ended 14 months of conflict, could pressure Hamas into concessions, though Israel‚Äôs goals in Gaza are broader and unresolved.‚Äã</p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-divider border-width="1px" border-style="solid" border-color="lightgrey" padding="10px 12px" />
      </mj-column>
    </mj-section>
