          A Russian court has ordered the <a href="https://www.france24.com/en/europe/20241126-russian-court-orders-arrest-of-france-24-journalist-who-reported-from-kursk" target="_blank">arrest</a> of FRANCE 24 senior reporter Catherine Norris Trent, accusing her of illegally crossing into the Kursk region from Ukraine. The charge stems from her reporting on the Ukrainian army‚Äôs summer incursion into Russian territory. The court‚Äôs decision follows a broader crackdown on Western journalists, including those from CNN, RAI, and Deutsche Welle, who were embedded with Ukrainian forces in Kursk. Russia has initiated criminal proceedings against these reporters in absentia, warning that they will be arrested if they enter the country.</p>
